7 NEW SECTION. Section 4. MAPPS council -- membership. (1) (a) There is an autonomous
8 MAPPS council with authority, consistent with legislative intent as stated in [section 2], to:
9 (i) assist the department of administration in choosing a program manager;
10 (ii) oversee the work of the program manager; and
11 (iii) develop a list of qualified education expenses.
12 (b) The council is allocated to the department of administration for administrative purposes, as
13 prescribed in 2-15-121(2), except as provided in this section.
14 (2) The council consists of five members who are appointed by the governor.
15 (3) Members appointed to the council shall represent a diverse group of stakeholders who are
16 supportive of MAPPS, including parents, grandparents, private school leaders and board members, education
17 entrepreneurs, and business leaders. All members of the council must have a demonstrated understanding of
18 and commitment to expanding educational options within the state as a valid public purpose necessary to
19 ensure equal educational opportunity for all children of the state, to preserve the liberty of parents to direct the
20 education of their children, and to enhance the economic competitiveness and cultural enrichment of the state.
21 (4) (a) Initial appointments to the council must be for staggered terms as follows:
22 (i) one member with a 4-year term designated as the initial presiding officer of the council for 2
23 years;
24 (ii) two members with 3-year terms; and
25 (iii) two members with 2-year terms.
26 (b) All terms after the initial term must be for 3 years. Appointment to the initial terms must be
27 made no later than 45 days following [the effective date of this act].
